RONALD CLARK WAS RELATING THE STORY OF HIS CHILDHOOD TO HIS DAUGHTER, JAMILAH.
HE SPOKE ABOUT HOW HE THOUGHT HIS FAMILY WAS RICH, BUT WAS TOLD BY HIS MOTHER THAT THEY WERE REALLY VERY POOR.
HIS DAD WAS OFFERED A JOB AS THE CUSTODIAN OF THE LIBRARY AND HE ACCEPTED AND THEY MOVED INTO THE LIBRARY.

HE WAS VERY PROUD OF THE JOB HIS FATHER DID,MAINTAINING THE LIBRARY SO THAT THE FLOORS AND THE BOOKSTACKS GLEAMED FROM THE WAX HIS DAD PUT ON. HE SPOKE OF HOW HE WAS ASHAMED TO INVITE FRIENDS OVER BECAUSE THEY THOUGHT OF HIM AS "THE KID WHO LIVED INTHE LIBRARY" WHICH HE WAS.
HE TOLD HER OF HOW HE LOVED THE LIBRARY.
HE COULD RUN AND JUMP AND PLAY AFTER CLOSING TIME EVEN THOUGH HE HAD TO BE VERY QUIET DURING LIBRARY OPEN HOURS.
HE WOULD GET OUT OF HIS BED AT NIGHT AND FIND ANSWERS TO HIS QUESTIONS, READING UNTIL 3 AM.

HIS LOVE OF READING AND GAINING KNOWLEDGE LED HIM TO BE THE FIRST PERSON IN HIS FAMILY TO GRADUATE HIGH SCHOOL AND GO ON TO COLLEGE, BECOMING PROFESSOR CLARK AND BRINGING HIS FATHER TO SEE HIS NAME ON HIS COLLEGE CLASSROOM DOOR.
HE SAID HE COULD TELL HOW MOVED HIS FATHER WAS BY THE LOOK ON HIS FACE; HIS FATHER WASN'T ONE FOR WORDS.
PROFESSOR CLARK WAS RELATING THE STORY OF HIS CHILDHOOD TO HIS DAUGHTER, JAMILAH.
HE TOLD HER HOW HE LIVED IN THE TEMPLE OF KNOWLEDGE, THE LIBRARY.
HIS FATHER WAS OFFERED A JOB AS THE CUSTODIAN OF THE LIBRARY.
THEY WERE VERY POOR SO HE ACCEPTED AND MOVED HIS FAMILY INTO THE LIBRARY. HE KEPT THE LIBRARY SPARKLING CLEAN, WAXING THE FLOORS AS WELL AS THE TOPS OF THE BOOKSHELVES.
IT WAS LIVING IN THE LIBRARY THAT CAUSED YOUNG RONALD TO LEARN TO LOVE READING AS A CHILD.
HE WOULD TAKE BOOKS TO BED AND READ UNTIL 3AM TO FIND ANSWERS TO QUESTIONS THAT HE HAD.
HE WAS ASHAMED TO INVITE FRIENDS OVER TO HIS HOUSE AS THEY CALLED HIM THE KID WHO LIVED IN THE LIBRARY, WHICH HE WAS.
RONALD WENT ON TO BECOME THE FIRST PERSON IN HIS FAMILY TO GRADUATE FROM HIGH SCHOOL AND COLLEGE. HE TOOK HIS FATHER TO SEE HIS CLASSROOM DOOR, WHICH HAD HIS NAME ON IT.
HIS FATHER WAS A VERY QUIET MAN BUT RONALD, THEN PROFESSOR CLARK, COULD TELL HE WAS VERY PROUD OF HIS SON.
JAMILAH CREATED THIS VIDEO TO SHARE THE REMARKABLE STORY OF HER FATHERS LIFE.
